===Etymology===
Ultimately from Persian {{FAchar|[[بخشیش]]}} (bakhšīš) ‘gift’, from {{FAchar|[[بخشیدن]]}} (bakhšīdan) ‘give’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/bækˈʃi:ʃ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A [[bribe]] or [[tip]] paid to speed up services. Used in the [[Middle East]] and [[Southwest]] [[Asia]]
#:''I got thru the checkpoint with a '''backsheesh'''.''

